#Setup AngularJS Environment

##Installation
1.	Download [Node Manager](https://nodejs.org/en/download/)

1.	Run the node-v4.2.4.pkg

1.	Click continue

1.	Click continue

1.	Click Agree

1.	Select :"Install for all users of this computer" and click continue

1.	Click Install
	
	It will be installed in /usr/local/bin so make sure 

	export PATH="/usr/local/bin:$PATH" and test with 
	
		npm -version

		npm install --global npm@latest
	
1.	Change permission

		sudo chown -R <username e.x:roybay> /usr/local/ 

1.	Install Grunt, Bower Package Manager and Yeoman 

		npm install --global yo bower grunt-cli

1.	Confirm installation 

		yo --version && bower --version && grunt --version

1.	Install Generators

		npm install --global generator-karma generator-angular 
	
		npm install --global phantomjs jasmine-core karma grunt-karma

##Working with Grunt
1.	Go to the root directory

1.	Run the npm 

		npm install 
		
1.	Run the bower 

		bower install 
		
1.	Run the Angular application 

		grunt serve 

1.	Run the karma test

		grunt test 

1.	Install packages

		bower install --save  <jquery-ui> 


	(bower.json is also be updated because of --save option)

1.	Make the lean version of the application

		grunt 

## Installing Protractor for E2E testing
1) Run
`npm install grunt-proctractor-runner`